Package: gammarus.phosphorum
Title: Population-level Tests of the Growth Rate Hypothesis in Gammarus
    fossarum
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Titouan", 
        family = "Dionet",
        role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
        email = "titouan.dionet@univ-lorraine.fr",
        comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0006-5602-1873")))
Description: A matrix-based framework for testing ecological stoichiometry
    theories at the population level. Integrates phosphorus content
    measurements with a size-structured population model for Gammarus
    fossarum to investigate whether the Growth Rate Hypothesis applies at
    the population level. Includes functions for matrix population
    modeling, stoichiometric calculations, and comprehensive simulation
    tools to explore the relationship between population growth rate and
    elemental composition.
